<abstract><t>The delivery of value-added services relies on the invocation of advanced Service Functions in a sequential order.  This mechanism is called Service Function Chaining (SFC).  The set of involved Service Functions and their order depends on the service context.  This document presents a set of use cases of Service Function Chaining (SFC).</t></abstract>

